<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7327> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7327" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The monetalis LENT MAR F., dated to 100 by Crawford (RRC 1.329, no. 329), is identified with the P. Lentulus of Cic. Brut. 136. Shackleton Bailey notes (as against Münzer and Crawford, above) that there is no evidence that he used the agnomen Marcellinus, but his descendants did (see Sumner, Orators 143, stemma). Add references to Crawford in MRR 2.437, and Index, 554." .
